President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has ordered that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff as a mark of respect for the U.S. service members and other victims who were killed in the terrorist attack on August 26, 2021, in Kabul, Afghanistan. This order applies to the White House, all public buildings and grounds, military posts and naval stations, and naval vessels of the Federal Government in the District of Columbia and throughout the United States and its Territories and possessions until sunset on August 30, 2021. The flag will also be flown at half-staff for the same duration at all United States embassies, legations, consular offices, and other facilities abroad, including military facilities and naval vessels and stations. This order was signed on August 26, 2021, by President Joseph R. Biden Jr.